text.__SUMMARY__: Pinus wangii, commonly known as the Guangdong white pine  (Chinese: 毛枝五针松), is a species of conifer in the family Pinaceae.
text.Distribution:
This pine tree is native to Yunnan Province of southern China, where two populations are known from Wenshan Prefecture. It is uncertain whether it occurs in northern Vietnam.Pinus wangii is an IUCN Red List Endangered species, threatened by continued logging. It is under second-class national protection in China.
